# Docker builds need only the three npm workspaces and the two root helpers
# they invoke. Keep unrelated repository files and local credentials out of
# the context by default instead of relying on an ever-growing denylist.
**
!LICENSE
!package-lock.json
!package.json
!release-toolchain.json
!scripts/
!scripts/canonicalize-package-modes.mjs
!scripts/fetch-pinned-npm.mjs
!packages/
!packages/agenc/
!packages/agenc/**
!packages/agenc-sdk/
!packages/agenc-sdk/**
!runtime/
!runtime/**

# Generated trees and common secret material remain excluded even beneath an
# allowed source directory. Published builds additionally use a checksum-bound
# Git context, so only reviewed tracked files can enter that boundary.
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/.env
**/.env.*
**/*.key
**/*.p12
**/*.pem
**/keys
packages/agenc/release
packages/agenc/release-artifacts
